I’m hoping pokemon battling being illegal in Rhyme city is more like a “city noise ordinance” than portrayed as an animal cruelty thing.

Because it would be a bad attempt at deconstruction thats been done many times otherwise.

Honestly “Pokemon Battles must be done outside city limits” is perfectly reasonable.

summary: Part of me wanted to binge watch all of the Pokémon anime movies before I end up going to see Detective Pikachu in theatres, but...
body:
Part of me wanted to binge watch all of the Pokémon anime movies before I end up going to see Detective Pikachu in theatres, but I got caught up with other stuff the last week and a half so I settled for just re-watching Mewtwo Strikes back today.

It isn’t a perfect movie by any stretch of the imagination. It’s pretty flawed in places, especially the dub with a lot of it’s more clueless changes and cuts. But honestly, I still and always will have a soft spot for it.

People can say whatever they want about the film, but it’s certainly enjoyable and it honestly does FEEL like Shudo and the Production team were trying really hard to make something meaningful. It may not be all that groundbreaking, but I can’t help but appreciate the effort, and it’s certainly a memorable experience. And Mewtwo is still my favourite character in the franchise to this day.

Maybe a lot of my enjoyment is nostalgia based. But so what, I’m proud that Pokémon was such a big part of my childhood, and I’ll be proud to have it as a big part of the entire rest of my life too.

And tomorrow I’ll proudly sit down in the theatre and cry a river of happy tears watching a live action Pokémon movie, because dang it I waited 2 decades for something like this and I’m going to cherish every second of it.
